The main section and the footer are present in the DOM but each carries the
`hidden` class, so both count as not shown: the chevron and the footer line
vanish, exactly as when the elements are absent (compare `header-empty.txtar`).
The whole page projects to a single line.
Pins: shown = present AND no `hidden` class; the `hidden` class hides a region as
completely as omitting it.

-- dom.html --
<section class="todoapp">
	<header class="header">
		<h1>todos</h1>
		<input class="new-todo" placeholder="What needs to be done?">
	</header>
	<section class="main hidden">
		<input id="toggle-all" class="toggle-all" type="checkbox">
		<label for="toggle-all">Mark all as complete</label>
		<ul class="todo-list"></ul>
	</section>
	<footer class="footer hidden">
		<span class="todo-count"><strong>0</strong> items left</span>
		<ul class="filters">
			<li><a class="selected" href="/">All</a></li>
			<li><a href="/active">Active</a></li>
			<li><a href="/completed">Completed</a></li>
		</ul>
	</footer>
</section>

-- projection.txt --
> ""
